Turkey Braces for Bureaucrat Resignation Storm, Aksam Says

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-03-02T06:37:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/turkey-braces-for-bureaucrat-resignation-storm-aksam-says.html
Approaching Turkish general
elections may spark a wave of resignations by senior bureaucrats
who are hoping to run as candidates for parliament, Aksam
newspaper reported.  The Ankara assembly may tomorrow approve June 12 as the
election date, meaning any civil servant who wants to run will
have to quit his or her position by March 15, the newspaper
said.  Senior bureaucrats who may transfer to political parties
include Treasury Undersecretary Ibrahim Canakci, Health
Undersecretary Nihat Tosun, Education Undersecretary Esengul
Civelek, Defence Undersecretary Murad Bayar, and Suleyman
Karaman, head of the state railways company, the newspaper said,
without saying how it got the information.  Erdogan Bayraktar, head of state construction company Toki,
is a possible candidate to join the ruling  Justice and
Development Party , Aksam said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
